## Veteran Voices: What Would Help Most

We asked respondents: "What one change would most improve your telehealth experience?"

**Top responses (in their words):**

1. **"Make it simpler to join"** (mentioned by 41%)
   - "One button, that's it"
   - "Stop making me log in three different places"
   - "Just send me a link that works"

2. **"Let me test before my appointment"** (mentioned by 34%)
   - "I want to know my camera works before I'm supposed to see my doctor"
   - "Send me a reminder the day before with a test link"
   
3. **"Better help when things go wrong"** (mentioned by 28%)
   - "A real person to call, not a robot"
   - "Someone who can see what I'm seeing and help me fix it"
   - "Don't make me start over from scratch"

4. **"Remember my settings"** (mentioned by 22%)
   - "Why do I have to allow my camera every single time?"
   - "My phone should just know how to do this by now"

5. **"More patience from providers"** (mentioned by 15%)
   - "Don't start the clock until I'm actually connected"
   - "Understand that this is hard for some of us"

